        <description>Email notification categories allow to identify and group related notifications that are listed in the notification settings for users. A notification, if active and subscribable, is listed in the selected Category in the notification preferences for each user (Notifications tab in the System Settings window).&#13;
&#13;
Do not leave the category as Uncategorized, as users may not be able to find the notification in their list of notifications.</description>
        <documentation_url>https://docs.servicenow.com/bundle/utah-platform-administration/page/administer/notification/task/t_CreateANotification.html</documentation_url>
        <finding_type>scan_finding</finding_type>
        <name>Avoid using Uncategorized notification category</name>
        <priority>3</priority>
        <resolution_details>When creating notification [sysevent_email_action], set the "Category" field value other than "Uncategorized" and pickup existing category. Existing notification categories would mostly suffice the purpose. &#13;
&#13;
However, new notification categories may also be created after discussing with ServiceNow platform team. This update is relevant for Architectural Approval. If not already done, please contact SNOWAA_Bayer_Platform_Architects@bayer.com to seek approval. &#13;
&#13;
To create new notification category&#13;
Navigate to All &gt; System Notification &gt; Email &gt; Notification Categories.</resolution_details>
